{
  "stem": "27507.10",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then we moved out-- all the time, my mother and I, we moved out of this area, old town of Warsaw, and found a place in the east part of Warsaw, on the other side of the Vistula in Praga, which is a quite a large part of Warsaw on the east side of the Vistula.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And we lived there for a week or so in one place, in one street.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And then there was a horrendous bombardment when we were there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But somehow, I was not afraid of the bombardment.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "We're standing down at the entrance to the-- on the ground floor in the courtyard.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And we saw the-- the lights of the reflectors in the sky seeking for the planes, and the bombs, and the-- the anti-aircraft fire, which was some of it was visible, and the bombs.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "It all came that were the Russians, Russian bombardment.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And some of it came very close.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We heard bombs very close.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But we were so happy to see them coming, all the same.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We were not-- the bombardments were something that was not bothering me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And later, I was actually sleeping through the bombardments, not even-- at Kopers, there was not, where we were later, there was no shelter anyway.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "There was a cellar, which was-- could maybe save you from a bullet if you-- but not from a bomb.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And so there was a-- but the bombardment somehow was not something to be afraid of.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And then we, again, changed place, and lived with some Ukrainian woman for a few days.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And my-- and my mother went somewhere.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And this Ukrainian woman took me by the hand, and took me somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "I think she decided that I was a risk factor in some way.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
